Section 1:
132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST REGULAR SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 731
An Act to Prohibit Municipalities from Barring the Creation of
Homeless Shelters
Reference to the Committee on State and Local Government suggested and ordered printed.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative LOOKNER of Portland.
Cosponsored by Senator BALDACCI of Penobscot and
Representatives: ARFORD of Brunswick, BRENNAN of Portland, BRIDGEO of Augusta,
CLOUTIER of Lewiston, DEBRITO of Waterville, EDER of Waterboro, SALISBURY of
Westbrook, SUPICA of Bangor.
Printed on recycled paper
1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 30-A MRSA §3015 is enacted to read:
3 §3015. Ordinances prohibiting homeless shelters
4 A municipality may not enact or enforce an ordinance that prohibits the creation or
5 operation of a homeless shelter.
6 SUMMARY
77 This bill prohibits municipalities from enacting or enforcing ordinances that prohibit
88 the creation or operation of a homeless shelter.
Page 1 - 132LR1340(01)
